contentrichtext.text: '''FPP''' may refer to: *[[Fundamental Physics Prize]] - the world's most lucrative science prize *[[First-past-the-post voting]], an electoral system whereby the governing party is determined by the number of seats won *[[First-person perspective]] - graphical perspective in video games *[[Farnesyl pyrophosphate]] *[[Fund Processing Passport]], document provided by promoters on their investment funds *[[Fixed-priority pre-emptive scheduling]], a task scheduling scheme with preemption and fixed priorities *The [[Binary black hole#The final-parsec problem|final-parsec problem]] for binary black holes *The [[first playable demo]] or First Playable Prototype (FPP) of a video game *[[Powership]], or Floating Power Plant (FPP) *Frequent Player Points (FPP), part of the reward system with the [[PokerStars]] VIP Club *Full Packaged Product (FPP) Software - a Microsoft term referring to the shrink-wrapped boxes of licensed product that can be purchased in a local retail store or any local software retailer. *[[Fantasy prone personality]], a disposition or personality trait in which a person experiences a lifelong extensive and deep involvement in fantasy. '''Organizations''': *[[Fire Protection Publications]], a publisher of firefighter training materials *[[Forest Peoples Programme]], a non-governmental organization concerned with indigenous peoples *[[Patriotic Front for Progress]] or ''Front Patriotique pour le Progrès'' (FPP), a political party in the Central African Republic *[[Portuguese Roller Sports Federation]] or ''Federação Portuguesa de Patinagem'' (FPP), the governing body for roller sports, such as rink hockey and figure skating, in Portugal {{disambig}}
